{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1080,"text":"Today I want to talk\nabout the meaning of words,"},{"time":4600,"text":"how we define them"},{"time":5920,"text":"and how they, almost as revenge,"},{"time":8200,"text":"define us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":9480,"text":"The English language\nis a magnificent sponge."},{"time":12560,"text":"I love the English language.\nI'm glad that I speak it."},{"time":15240,"text":"But for all that, it has a lot of holes."},{"time":18480,"text":"In Greek, there's a word, \"lachesism\""},{"time":20840,"text":"which is the hunger for disaster."},{"time":24720,"text":"You know, when you see\na thunderstorm on the horizon"},{"time":28320,"text":"and you just find yourself\nrooting for the storm."},{"time":32080,"text":"In Mandarin, they have a word \"yù yī\" --"},{"time":34040,"text":"I'm not pronouncing that correctly --"},{"time":36080,"text":"which means the longing\nto feel intensely again"},{"time":39800,"text":"the way you did when you were a kid."},{"time":43680,"text":"In Polish, they have a word \"jouska\""},{"time":46840,"text":"which is the kind of\nhypothetical conversation"},{"time":50400,"text":"that you compulsively\nplay out in your head."},{"time":54400,"text":"And finally, in German,\nof course in German,"},{"time":57560,"text":"they have a word called \"zielschmerz\""},{"time":60440,"text":"which is the dread\nof getting what you want."}]},{"cues":[{"time":63880,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":68000,"text":"Finally fulfilling a lifelong dream."},{"time":71840,"text":"I'm German myself,\nso I know exactly what that feels like."}]},{"cues":[{"time":75120,"text":"Now, I'm not sure\nif I would use any of these words"},{"time":77760,"text":"as I go about my day,"},{"time":79440,"text":"but I'm really glad they exist."},{"time":81600,"text":"But the only reason they exist\nis because I made them up."}]},{"cues":[{"time":85360,"text":"I am the author of \"The Dictionary\nof Obscure Sorrows,\""},{"time":89000,"text":"which I've been writing\nfor the last seven years."},{"time":92120,"text":"And the whole mission of the project"},{"time":94160,"text":"is to find holes\nin the language of emotion"},{"time":99360,"text":"and try to fill them"},{"time":100600,"text":"so that we have a way of talking\nabout all those human peccadilloes"},{"time":104520,"text":"and quirks of the human condition"},{"time":106960,"text":"that we all feel\nbut may not think to talk about"},{"time":110960,"text":"because we don't have the words to do it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":113680,"text":"And about halfway through this project,"},{"time":116120,"text":"I defined \"sonder,\""},{"time":117760,"text":"the idea that we all think of ourselves\nas the main character"},{"time":121160,"text":"and everyone else is just extras."},{"time":123840,"text":"But in reality,\nwe're all the main character,"},{"time":126560,"text":"and you yourself are an extra\nin someone else's story."},{"time":131160,"text":"And so as soon as I published that,"},{"time":134280,"text":"I got a lot of response from people"},{"time":136000,"text":"saying, \"Thank you for giving voice\nto something I had felt all my life"},{"time":140640,"text":"but there was no word for that.\""},{"time":143680,"text":"So it made them feel less alone."},{"time":146160,"text":"That's the power of words,"},{"time":148880,"text":"to make us feel less alone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":152400,"text":"And it was not long after that"},{"time":154160,"text":"that I started to notice sonder"},{"time":155960,"text":"being used earnestly\nin conversations online,"},{"time":160280,"text":"and not long after I actually noticed it,"},{"time":163200,"text":"I caught it next to me\nin an actual conversation in person."},{"time":166720,"text":"There is no stranger feeling\nthan making up a word"},{"time":169200,"text":"and then seeing it\ntake on a mind of its own."},{"time":173520,"text":"I don't have a word\nfor that yet, but I will."}]},{"cues":[{"time":175640,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":177080,"text":"I'm working on it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":179600,"text":"I started to think\nabout what makes words real,"},{"time":183560,"text":"because a lot of people ask me,"},{"time":185080,"text":"the most common thing\nI got from people is,"},{"time":187440,"text":"\"Well, are these words made up?\nI don't really understand.\""},{"time":190720,"text":"And I didn't really know what to tell them"},{"time":192800,"text":"because once sonder started to take off,"},{"time":194760,"text":"who am I to say what words\nare real and what aren't."},{"time":198160,"text":"And so I sort of felt like Steve Jobs,\nwho described his epiphany"},{"time":202240,"text":"as when he realized that most of us,\nas we go through the day,"},{"time":205720,"text":"we just try to avoid\nbouncing against the walls too much"},{"time":208760,"text":"and just sort of get on with things."},{"time":211880,"text":"But once you realize that people --"},{"time":216280,"text":"that this world was built\nby people no smarter than you,"},{"time":220080,"text":"then you can reach out\nand touch those walls"},{"time":222200,"text":"and even put your hand through them"},{"time":223920,"text":"and realize that you have\nthe power to change it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":227080,"text":"And when people ask me,\n\"Are these words real?\""},{"time":230760,"text":"I had a variety of answers\nthat I tried out."},{"time":232880,"text":"Some of them made sense.\nSome of them didn't."},{"time":235040,"text":"But one of them I tried out was,"},{"time":236640,"text":"\"Well, a word is real\nif you want it to be real.\""},{"time":240200,"text":"The way that this path is real\nbecause people wanted it to be there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":244440,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":246160,"text":"It happens on college\ncampuses all the time."},{"time":248280,"text":"It's called a \"desire path.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":249640,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":250680,"text":"But then I decided,\nwhat people are really asking"},{"time":253040,"text":"when they're asking if a word is real,\nthey're really asking,"},{"time":255960,"text":"\"Well, how many brains\nwill this give me access to?\""},{"time":261079,"text":"Because I think that's\na lot of how we look at language."},{"time":263840,"text":"A word is essentially a key"},{"time":266640,"text":"that gets us into certain people's heads."},{"time":269640,"text":"And if it gets us into one brain,"},{"time":272920,"text":"it's not really worth it,"},{"time":274200,"text":"not really worth knowing."},{"time":275480,"text":"Two brains, eh, it depends on who it is."},{"time":277960,"text":"A million brains, OK, now we're talking."},{"time":280800,"text":"And so a real word is one that gets you\naccess to as many brains as you can."},{"time":287280,"text":"That's what makes it worth knowing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":290560,"text":"Incidentally, the realest word of all\nby this measure is this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":294400,"text":"[O.K.]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":296640,"text":"That's it."},{"time":297880,"text":"The realest word we have."},{"time":299160,"text":"That is the closest thing we have\nto a master key."},{"time":301760,"text":"That's the most commonly\nunderstood word in the world,"},{"time":304360,"text":"no matter where you are."},{"time":305640,"text":"The problem with that is,"},{"time":306880,"text":"no one seems to know\nwhat those two letters stand for."}]},{"cues":[{"time":309600,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":311920,"text":"Which is kind of weird, right?"},{"time":314000,"text":"I mean, it could be a misspelling\nof \"all correct,\" I guess,"},{"time":317480,"text":"or \"old kinderhook.\""},{"time":318760,"text":"No one really seems to know,\nbut the fact that it doesn't matter"},{"time":322640,"text":"says something about\nhow we add meaning to words."},{"time":326160,"text":"The meaning is not\nin the words themselves."},{"time":329920,"text":"We're the ones\nthat pour ourselves into it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":333440,"text":"And I think, when we're all searching\nfor meaning in our lives,"},{"time":338040,"text":"and searching for the meaning of life,"},{"time":339920,"text":"I think words have\nsomething to do with that."},{"time":344040,"text":"And I think if you're looking\nfor the meaning of something,"},{"time":346840,"text":"the dictionary is a decent place to start."},{"time":349760,"text":"It brings a sense of order"},{"time":352160,"text":"to a very chaotic universe."},{"time":354880,"text":"Our view of things is so limited"},{"time":357560,"text":"that we have to come up\nwith patterns and shorthands"},{"time":360360,"text":"and try to figure out\na way to interpret it"},{"time":362680,"text":"and be able to get on with our day."},{"time":365240,"text":"We need words to contain us,\nto define ourselves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":369400,"text":"I think a lot of us feel boxed in"},{"time":372320,"text":"by how we use these words."},{"time":373920,"text":"We forget that words are made up."},{"time":376280,"text":"It's not just my words.\nAll words are made up,"},{"time":379280,"text":"but not all of them mean something."},{"time":381880,"text":"We're all just sort of\ntrapped in our own lexicons"},{"time":386000,"text":"that don't necessarily correlate\nwith people who aren't already like us,"},{"time":390760,"text":"and so I think I feel us drifting apart\na little more every year,"},{"time":395400,"text":"the more seriously we take words."}]},{"cues":[{"time":399880,"text":"Because remember, words are not real."},{"time":403600,"text":"They don't have meaning. We do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":406480,"text":"And I'd like to leave you with a reading"},{"time":409760,"text":"from one of my favorite philosophers,"},{"time":412400,"text":"Bill Watterson, who created\n\"Calvin and Hobbes.\""},{"time":414960,"text":"He said,"},{"time":417040,"text":"\"Creating a life that reflects\nyour values and satisfies your soul"},{"time":420880,"text":"is a rare achievement."},{"time":422560,"text":"To invent your own life's meaning"},{"time":425040,"text":"is not easy,"},{"time":426600,"text":"but it is still allowed,"},{"time":428440,"text":"and I think you'll be\nhappier for the trouble.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":431320,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":432560,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}